         <abstract>
            <p>The inversive congruential method with prime modulus for generating uniform pseudorandom numbers is studied. Lower bounds for the discrepancy of k-tuples of successive pseudorandom numbers are established, which improve earlier results of Niederreiter. Moreover, the present proof is substantially simpler than the earlier one.</p>
          </abstract>
